94
00:05:15,649 --> 00:05:17,859
Just looking at him.
Like, "I've got the light.

95
00:05:17,943 --> 00:05:20,278
You know I've got the light.
You know I've got that light."

96
00:05:24,366 --> 00:05:26,201
I was running behind him, all apologetic.

97
00:05:26,284 --> 00:05:27,953
"I'm sorry, I didn't know.
He-- I'm sorry.

98
00:05:28,036 --> 00:05:30,914
I would have stopped--
I've never done this before."

99
00:05:36,211 --> 00:05:39,464
I walked with that man for 12 blocks.

100
00:05:41,716 --> 00:05:43,843
And let me tell you,
I have never been imbued

101
00:05:43,927 --> 00:05:45,929
with the confidence of another human being

102
00:05:46,596 --> 00:05:48,181
the way I was with him.

103
00:05:49,224 --> 00:05:50,684
I started that day...

104
00:05:52,143 --> 00:05:55,188
thinking and pondering
before stepping out.

105
00:05:56,565 --> 00:05:58,316
And after a few blocks with him,

106
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:00,277
I started believing.

107
00:06:01,945 --> 00:06:05,657
And after eight blocks,
it was the only way I knew how to live.

108
00:06:06,908 --> 00:06:10,287
I had my phone out.
I was tweeting and texting.

109
00:06:10,829 --> 00:06:12,914
I didn't play games.
I'd be looking down, look up.

110
00:06:12,998 --> 00:06:14,332
The light would change, and I was out.

111
00:06:14,416 --> 00:06:19,212
I didn't care if a truck or a train
